A driver is dead after his car apparently left a road in Coon Rapids and crashed into a tree. The man was southbound near the 11000 block of Foley Boulevard NW. at 7:41 a.m. Tuesday when the crash happened, according to Coon Rapids police. Coon Rapids police and fire departments and Allina EMS responded with lifesaving efforts but the man died at a hospital, according to a police statement. Officers are investigating the incident.   